div.div:
Kirishima Tooru was accustomed to solving all problems through violence and was called “the Demon of Sakuragi.” One day, the boss of the Sakuragi family suddenly summons Kirishima and appoints him caretaker of his only daughter, Yaeka! A heartwarming comedy about a yakuza crime family’s right-hand man and the boss’ only daughter. The two of them are about to begin their new daily lives together!
(Source: Crunchyroll, edited)
Genjitsu Shugi Yuusha no Oukoku Saikenki

Suddenly summoned to a fantasy world and betrothed to the princess, Kazuya Souma is crowned the new king after providing the royal family with impressive advice. To rule the kingdom, he's taking the nontraditional (and very human) route of administrative reform. In a realm of dragons and elves, will this revolutionary's unique path prove effective?
(Source: Funimation)
Comedy, Drama, Romance, Slice of Life

"What am I doing?" Yuuhi Nagi's high school life is already halfway over, but he still doesn't have any dreams, ambitions, or even friends in his class! Every day is boring, until he's suddenly in danger of getting held back! A bittersweet high school drama made up of 4 potential grade repeaters with the worst grades in the class and 1 student acting as their teacher!
(Source: Pocket Comics)

“There are no sane men left in this world. They're like ghosts, mimicking their past behaviors and assaulting any woman they see. They've turned into beasts.”
Anezaki Satoru had a precious childhood friend, Ichinose Yuna, who was killed by a gang of rapists. Blinded by rage and thirst for revenge, Satoru gruesomely murdered 15 rapists and cut off their genitals, for which he was sentenced to capital punishment. After his death, Satoru regains consciousness in another world where all men have become mindless beasts. Finding himself lost in this world, he meets some of the struggling survivors fighting the hordes of beasts. What he learns is shocking... Yuna is apparently still alive in this world! Satoru chooses to join the fight in order to find his precious friend.
(Source: Comikey)
